cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a novel distributed optimization framework for black-box adversarial attacks on deep convolutional neural networks. This involves the use of error-correcting codes to mitigate the effects of stragglers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the application involves deep convolutional neural networks. The paper also involves distributed computing, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of evolutionary strategies and structured exploration methods could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
